The Eccentric Woodland is an existential logistics problem for Rakuen. Every path closure, forged escort seal, or territorial fight inside the woodland translates directly into shortages and governance stress inside Rakuen — the city has no alternative southern supply corridor. Rakuen maintains three Dispatch Houses managing guide-compact agreements with different woodland territorial operators: one at the woodland entry point, one in the Causeway Quarter, and one in the Upper Ring. The predecessor-compact problem is politically sensitive: former path-warden operators whose contracts with Rakuen expired during disaster years continued exercising territorial authority without legitimating compact, and they know the route structures and cargo profiles of Rakuen-bound convoys better than any newcomer. Attributing specific predation incidents to lapsed compacts would constitute public admission that Rakuen's supply failures created the threat. During Cinderteeth ash years, visibility collapse and poisoned runoff compounded woodland route uncertainty into city-scale supply emergencies. All three Rakuen annexation petitions to Midgaard cited woodland instability; Midgaard's refusal cited the same instability as the reason integration was impractical — a circularity Rakuen cannot break without either resolving the woodland problem itself or forcing Midgaard to resolve it.

